  "prompt": "Are non-living things made up of cells?",
  "response": "No, non-living things are not made up of cells. Cells are the basic structural and functional units of living organisms. They are the building blocks of life, found in plants, animals, fungi, and microorganisms. Non-living things, such as rocks, water, and metals, do not contain cells and are composed of different materials and structures that do not exhibit the characteristics of life, such as metabolism, growth, and reproduction.",
